NE liability. Classic secondary amide: electrophilic carbonyl carbon (q=+0.26), C-N BO 1.32, ground-state resonance modest. The bond the whole project aims to protect.\",\n}\n\nqdf['carbonyl_electrophile'] = qdf['molecule'].map(carbonyl)\nqdf['inertness_rank'] = qdf['molecule'].map(inert_rank)\nqdf['hydrolytic_verdict'] = qdf['molecule'].map(verdict)\nqdf = qdf.sort_values('inertness_rank').reset_index(drop=True)\n\ncols = ['inertness_rank','molecule','linkage','scissile_atoms','wiberg_bond_order',\n        'q_atomA','q_atomB_N','charge_sep','carbonyl_electrophile','hydrolytic_verdict']\nqdf = qdf[cols]\nqdf.to_csv(\"hydrolytic_stability_qm.csv\", index=False)\nprint(qdf[['inertness_rank','molecule','wiberg_bond_order','q_atomA','carbonyl_electrophile']].to_string(index=False))\nprint(\"\\nMethod: GFN2-xTB, --opt --alpb water, neutral acid form, full molecules (32-35 atoms), all converged.\")\n"}

